         Given:  SB is a PvP game.  The normal player will be exposed to PvP.<BR>Given:  People dont like to lose.  If they lose more than 80% of the time they will probably quit.<BR>Given:  There is a great deal of resistance to quitting your character.<P>Myself, Hed, and perhaps 4 handpicked others from our respective guilds could go into SB right now and after a week or 2 of catching up in xp we could hand down beatings to everyone there.  I mean like kill them all 50 of them 20 times over and suffering only a handfull of losses.<P>After 15-20 consecutive deaths someone will come to the realization that a slow, hulking character with great melee skills is totally useless when facing a highly mobile group, armed with powerful ranged attacks.<P>This guy will be faced with the choice of giving up this character who he has given the nickname he's been using since 8th grade, the character he's based on a beloved a character in a book he's read years ago.  A character he's been planning on playing is SB for the last year.  Simply put, one he's attached to.<P>He's not going to just dump this character and start over with a radical PvP template without a second thought.   More likely he's going to hit the boards or start emailing.  "Whaaa!  Nerf Archers!!!!  Nerf Mages!!!  Booohoo, my poor character!  He's dying!"   Heard that before?  UO, EQ, AC, they have all heard the cries to nerf the archer and the mage.<P>If they dont nerf he's gonna quit and go play EQ.   If they do nerf now everyone with a mage or archer is going to be pissed off, and rightly so, because they just got fucked over.<P>It's not Mr Melee's fault.  He just made the character he wanted, and one that he expected to be good.  One that probably WAS good with respect to PvM, but PvP is a whole different ball game, one where melee is usally a last ditch effort. <P>WP said there is no perma death.  I say there is.  Any character that's designed with PvM in mind is a death sentance in a PvP game.  These characters will be abandoned, and probably deleted very quickly.  Many times the player will be done with the game.  <P>So tell me.  Is losing players who could have been competitive a problem?  Is dooming players to delete thier characters because they cant even pvp on a most rudimentary level a problem?<BR>
