         24.  <b>"RE: Looting forces the issue"</b></FONT></TD></TR>
      <TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><td colspan="2" width="100%">
         <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#c0c0c0">
         <blockquote>
         Xp loss will hurt more than the non-bound items I'm sure.  But either way, the point remains.<P>Not surprisingly devs make games to be played the way they expect them to be played.   EQ, for example, makes the false assumption that players should want to xp in a group, and penalizes those who do not join one.  Such mistakes are only amplified in a PvP environment.   <P>WP is also making assumptions about how thier game will be played.  They seem to be assuming that fights will take place for political reasons, not just because it's more efficient to kill players than MOBs.  There is a grouping xp bonus and you get xp for killing players.   Why not get a group together and kill players?  Players will also offer up more loot than MOBs even if the best pieces are bound.  You'll still get all the cash and some items.<P>The guy on the other end is going to walk away from the gangbang being down in xp and down in cash.  He could quite possibly lose more than he gained while xping off MOBs.   How long will someone who played for 8 hrs only to lose everything he got to getting gangraped a few times stay in your game?
         </blockquote></FONT></TD></TR>
