      <TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><td colspan="2" width="100%">
         <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#c0c0c0">
         <blockquote>
         Equality - all players have the same character capabilities/powers/approximate hit points etc. Players do not gain advantage playing 24/7.<P>Perception - advantages are gained based on a players understanding of the game - (spell interaction) etc<P>Discipline-players gain advantage by trusting thier approach to PvP,(Making and sticking with a plan in singles or teams,developed through practice and trial and error)<P>Creativity- When the shit hits the fan, does the player stay composed,and resourceful? A player that can is successful.<P>Spite<P>&lt;Fine, design a game of 10,000-sided chess that involves little fantasy people that run around and kill each other on a computer screen, and the game never ends&gt;<BR>      Hey asshole it was called NwN.<P><BR>
