         If you require different classes to accomplish certain tasks, you favor the masses rather than the individual.  A generic class allows individual skill to govern achievement rather than the proper combination of classes with the right cohesion at the appropriate level.<P>A difference in classes accomplishes nothing at all, in that it leaves each class wanting something more powerful or more well-rounded.  Just look at the EQ class system.
