         30.  <b>"LOL"</b></FONT></TD></TR>
      <TR BGCOLOR="#000000"><td colspan="2" width="100%">
         <FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#c0c0c0">
         <blockquote>
         Yeah, but one or more of those "features" is often brought up as a reason NwN is so revered after the fact -- the community was smaller, more insular, and everybody could /almost/ know who everyone else was, just because the server wasn't meant to support more than a few hundred people at any time. Plus everyone was blowing their kid's inheritances on dialup fees, further limiting the number of people who could afford to play at all.<P>But there are people who get misty-eyed listening to the tinny 8-bit theme music at <a href="http://neverwinter.bladekeep.com" target="_blank">Medar's archive site</a>, who want their 1,000-sided chess game and have good reasons for wanting to play it. Most know better than to expect those halcyon days to come again.<P>J.<BR>damned vulpine<BR><a href="http://sb.xrgaming.net/" target="_blank">http://sb.xrgaming.net/</a>
